Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Chop @eggplant{1%unit} into 1-inch cubes. Core and seed @red bell pepper{1%unit}, then chop into 1-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until starting to brown, about ~{20%minutes}.

Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1%unit}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Slice @green olives{1%ounce} into small rounds. Halve @ciabatta bread{1%unit}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onions and garlic. Cook until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @ground pork{8%ounce}, break up into small pieces, and cook until browned, about ~{5%minutes}.

Add @diced tomatoes{1%box}, olives, @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, and 1/2 cup water to pan. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until thickened, about ~{10%minutes}. Stir in roasted veggies, and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @italian seasoning{1%tbsp} (to taste).

> TIP: If you'd prefer a less tart caponata, add 1 tsp sugar.

Place ciabatta halves in oven, and toast until golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once toasted, rub with remaining @garlic{1%clove}, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spoon caponata into bowls, and serve with toasted ciabatta.